            "verbal": {
              "value": true
            },
            "somatic": {
              "value": true
            },
            "material": {
              "value": false
            },
            "description": {
              "value": "* You create a tiny, harmless sensory effect that predicts what the weather will be at your location for the next 24 hours. The effect might manifest as a golden orb for clear skies, a cloud for rain, falling snowflakes for snow, and so on. This effect persists for 1 round.\n\n* You instantly make a flower bloom, a seed pod open, or a leaf bud bloom.\n\n* You create an instantenous, harmless sensory effect, such as falling leaves, a puff of wind, the sound of a small animal, or the faint order of skunk. The effect must fit in a 5-foot cube.\n\n* You instantly light or snuff out a candle, a torch, or a small campfire."
            },
